-- Sanity-test: use ring/field on Real to see if the error messages
-- guide an LLM through fixes.

module Test.llm_dogfood_test

import Real.basics
import Real.addition
import Real.multiplication
import Real.negation
import Real.ring
import Real.algebra

-- (1) Difference of squares — DEFERRED: ring v2's cross-pair
-- cancellation isn't wired in yet. Error: "proveMultiplyMerge with
-- cross-pair cancellations not yet supported".

-- (2) Square of sum — DEFERRED: a*b + b*a canonicalises to 2(a*b),
-- and v2 rejects |coeff| > 1. Error said so verbatim.

-- (3) Triple product expansion.
theorem Real.expand_three (a b c : Real)
        : (a + b) * c = a * c + b * c := ring

-- (4) Negation through product — DEFERRED: Real doesn't yet have
-- `multiply_negate_left` as a library axiom. The error said exactly
-- which axiom was missing, so an LLM can either add the lemma to
-- Real/algebra.math (using Ring.multiply_negate_left from
-- Algebra/ring_lemmas.math + Real.is_ring) or skip the test.
